1
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,780
=Auspicious Nobles=

2
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,940
=Episode 9=

3
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,500
(If You Keep This Up,
My Husband Will Be Jealous)

4
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:57,110
(My little pink paradise...)

5
00:00:57,110 --> 00:00:58,880
(My cute hanging ornaments,
my bright rug...)

6
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,840
(Zheng Yuanhe, you have zero taste!)

7
00:01:00,850 --> 00:01:02,200
(You took the decompression room
that I decorated)

8
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,280
(and turned it into this mess.)

9
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,350
Do you like this place?

10
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:11,040
Yes.

11
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:15,620
Then I shall give it to you.

12
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,630
The Pan Residence
is crowded and chaotic,

13
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,940
but no one will disturb you here.

14
00:01:19,420 --> 00:01:20,260
You can stay here

15
00:01:20,260 --> 00:01:22,060
and focus on doing
what you like in peace.

16
00:01:25,610 --> 00:01:26,180
Here it comes.

17
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,220
(This scheming fool
is giving me Wangshi Tower)

18
00:01:28,220 --> 00:01:29,460
(obviously to test me.)

19
00:01:30,180 --> 00:01:31,380
Oh, no.

20
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:33,020
This gift is far too valuable.

21
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:34,980
As a mere housewife,
I cannot accept this.

22
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:38,380
If my husband found out,

23
00:01:38,460 --> 00:01:39,420
he would misunderstand.

24
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:40,940
I can't take it.

25
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,020
Well,

26
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:48,820
are you free tomorrow?

27
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,660
Could you come
and guide me in making crossbows?

28
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:52,020
We'll see about that.

29
00:01:52,030 --> 00:01:53,320
There are so many chores at home,

30
00:01:53,330 --> 00:01:55,500
and I still have to take care
of my husband's daily needs.

31
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,520
Let's talk after I'm done.

32
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,020
(No matter what tricks he's playing,)

33
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:16,680
(I must minimize my contact
with him from now on.)

34
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:17,700
(He's too dangerous.)

35
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,820
(Zhao Prince's Residence)

36
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:27,900
How are our KPI for this month?

37
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,300
Just give me whatever amount
you've collected first.

38
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:32,060
(If I don't pay them soon,)

39
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,160
(Jiuzhu and the rest
will literally bury me alive.)

40
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:36,540
We have a total zero yield.

41
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:40,100
Not only did my brother shut down
the rice ball stall you had me open,

42
00:02:41,020 --> 00:02:41,740
but recently,

43
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:44,180
he has also been cracking down
on my imperial businesses everywhere.

44
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,660
Several of our trade routes

45
00:02:45,660 --> 00:02:47,420
were cut off by him
under various pretexts.

46
00:02:47,660 --> 00:02:48,860
Even the businesses

47
00:02:49,220 --> 00:02:50,220
you invested in before

48
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,990
have lost more
than half of their profits.

49
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,420
The darn Crown Prince
is like a piece of gum.

50
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:56,290
Once he sticks to you,
you can't get rid of him.

51
00:02:57,860 --> 00:02:58,500
Tower Master,

52
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:00,140
if I fall from power,

53
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:02,100
you will lose yet another partner
in the capital

54
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:04,020
who can shield you
from the wind and rain.

55
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,660
Don't you try to play
mind games with me.

56
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:10,700
I'm not getting involved
in your succession war with Yuanhe.

57
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:11,940
As heaven is my witness,

58
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:14,180
I really just want to make money.

59
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:15,580
Tower Master,

60
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,780
my brother holds
immense power right now.

61
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:19,990
It seems we must find an alternative way

62
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,740
if we want to make money safely.

63
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:24,100
Going head-to-head won't work.

64
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:27,940
How can I make him detest me

65
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:30,060
yet not dare to get rid of me?

66
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:36,500
By becoming an idol!

67
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:39,900
(Once I become a national idol)

68
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,460
(with millions of fans,)

69
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,300
(if that guy wants
to lay a hand on me again,)

70
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:45,380
(he'll have to consider
the public backlash.)

71
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:48,500
An idol?

72
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:50,540
What is that?

73
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:52,180
We'll start a newspaper.

74
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:53,420
A newspaper?

75
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:55,860
And what is a newspaper?

76
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,220
Well, a newspaper

77
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,820
is a sheet of paper filled with

78
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:01,940
essays, poems, and interesting news.

79
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:03,500
We'll publish it regularly

80
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:06,340
so that everyone can buy and read it.

81
00:04:07,220 --> 00:04:08,380
A thin sheet of paper

82
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,340
can make money

83
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,420
and counter Yuanhe at the same time?

84
00:04:13,860 --> 00:04:15,780
This is the power of public opinion.

85
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:17,060
When the time comes,

86
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,940
I will publish poems in the newspaper.

87
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,820
As long as the poems become a hit,

88
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:23,860
I'll be a scholar renowned
throughout the land.

89
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,980
With reputation and
public support on our side,

90
00:04:26,180 --> 00:04:28,340
if the darn Crown Prince
dares to cross us again,

91
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:30,300
he will have to think twice.

92
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:32,460
(Once this is established,)

93
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,990
(we will be able to
manipulate public opinion nationwide.)

94
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:37,100
(To think of such a method,)

95
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,380
(who really are you?)

96
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,460
I can also make
some money as an influencer.

97
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:44,740
(Pan Residence)

98
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:48,020
(Qingqing Elegant Courtyard)

99
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:53,060
Look at this.

100
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:57,740
(The Wangshi Chronicle: Poetry,
Gossip, Weekly Serials, Cat Finder)

101
00:04:58,460 --> 00:04:59,300
A piece of paper.

102
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:02,860
No, no, no.

103
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:05,380
This is a newspaper.

104
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:07,780
(The Wangshi Chronicle)

105
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:11,460
Whether we can make
our fortune again depends on it.

106
00:05:13,420 --> 00:05:14,660
Tower Master,

107
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,380
it's just a piece of paper.

108
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:17,700
Is it really that powerful?

109
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:20,220
You don't know the power of publicity.

110
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:21,420
Look here.

111
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,220
(Poetry)
We put poetry on the front page.

112
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:24,660
Gossip on the second page.

113
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,020
(Novel Content)
A serialized novel on the third page.

114
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:29,500
You left the fourth page blank

115
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,860
and wrote "For Sale".

116
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:32,020
What does that mean?

117
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:33,380
Advertising space.

118
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:35,700
In the future, if anyone

119
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,180
wants to promote their goods,

120
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,980
they can place an ad right here.

121
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:43,540
For example,

122
00:05:43,780 --> 00:05:45,980
"New arrivals at Zhang's Silk Shop,

123
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:48,540
10% off new dishes at Li's Restaurant."

124
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:49,500
And

125
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:52,660
we will charge them
by the line and by the word.

126
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:57,220
Since we are making
a newspaper just to put up ads,

127
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,500
then all of these other pages

128
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:00,600
should be turned into
ad spaces to make more money.

129
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:05,340
You silly girl.

130
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:09,060
To make the newspaper
the ultimate promotional tool,

131
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:11,540
we must turn everyone into our fans.

132
00:06:11,820 --> 00:06:14,060
When everyone,
from high officials to commoners,

133
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:16,180
follows our newspaper every single day,

134
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:17,180
then

135
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:18,700
people will pay premium prices

136
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:19,860
to buy our ad space.

137
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,390
Even if I explain it,
you wouldn't understand.

138
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,860
This way, the brothers
won't be sitting idle.

139
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:32,900
They can sell newspapers
on the streets every day.

140
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:35,060
They can make money
while gathering intelligence.

141
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,360
Killing multiple birds with one stone.

142
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:37,180
You

143
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:39,100
want us to be errand boys?

144
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,260
Well, it's better than doing nothing.

145
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:48,740
By the way,

146
00:06:49,020 --> 00:06:52,820
my business suffered
heavy losses recently.

147
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:55,100
Money is a bit tight right now.

148
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:57,660
Can you

149
00:06:58,660 --> 00:07:00,620
not ask for money all the time?

150
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,820
We have over
8,000 brothers to feed and house.

151
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,150
The rice balls can't be sold,

152
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:06,700
but we still need to buy intelligence.

153
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:07,780
This money

154
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:09,420
naturally has to be paid.

155
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:10,660
When I asked you to find people

156
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:12,460
to protect the Wangshi Tower properties,

157
00:07:12,580 --> 00:07:14,140
who told you to get that many people?

158
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:15,560
It's useless to talk about this now.

159
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:16,780
No money, no talk.

160
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,100
Pay first, work later.

161
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,300
You said it yourself.

162
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:26,260
Jiuzhu,

163
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:29,140
don't be so narrow-minded.

164
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:31,580
Once everyone
accepts the Wangshi Chronicle,

165
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:34,380
it will become
a massive traffic-driving platform.

166
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:36,140
By then, whatever we publish

167
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,180
will set the trend.

168
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:38,580
Whatever we sell, people will buy.

169
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:41,660
That is an enormous commercial value.

170
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:43,300
And you

171
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,700
will be the logistics director
of a major corporation.

172
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,780
You're completely obsessed with money.

173
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:01,180
You have no business vision.

174
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:04,980
Tower Master.

175
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:05,940
Come on in.

176
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:11,380
As you ordered, Tower Master,

177
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:13,100
(Wang, Secret Guard of Wangshi Tower)
we have been keeping an eye on Li Muyan.

178
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,020
(Wang, Secret Guard of Wangshi Tower)
We recently learned

179
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:16,100
that she plans
to harm Pan Yang's mother.

180
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:18,860
What did you say?

181
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:20,420
She approached me

182
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:22,970
and wanted me to intentionally
hit Pan Yang's mother with a cart.

183
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:24,380
Then she would step in to save her.

184
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:26,460
What a wicked woman.

185
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:28,060
She knows Mother is good to me,

186
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,790
so she wants to direct
and act in this play herself.

187
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:32,120
This is making me furious.

188
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,180
What should I do then?

189
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:38,700
Just do exactly as she said for now.

190
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,300
When the time comes,

191
00:08:40,620 --> 00:08:43,420
I'll show her
the real power of our newspaper.

192
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,180
Sugar-coated haws.
Get your sugar-coated haws.

193
00:08:48,180 --> 00:08:49,900
- Qingqing hasn't had sugar figurines in a long time.
- Ma'am, why not buy a stick?

194
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,500
She will be delighted to see this.

195
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,900
We have sugar figurines
and sugar-coated haws.

196
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,020
That dead old woman

197
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,420
only remembers what that jerk likes.

198
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:56,540
Horse.

199
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,620
Do you see her clearly?

200
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:58,700
Yes, I do.

201
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,980
Ram into her as hard as you can.

202
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:02,880
It would be best
if she stays bedridden for life.

203
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:05,900
You are a straightforward lady.

204
00:09:05,910 --> 00:09:07,900
People in our line of work
admire people like you.

205
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:09,300
No, thank you.

206
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:10,300
I'll take this one.

207
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,380
Alright.

208
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:13,500
Here is the money. Keep it safe.

209
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:15,180
Ma'am,

210
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,740
my cart is about to crash into you.

211
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:17,960
Please get out of the way. Move!

212
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:20,300
It's about to hit you. Watch out. Move!

213
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:30,200
- That was so dangerous.
- Exactly.

214
00:09:30,220 --> 00:09:30,620
Beautiful lady.

215
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:31,100
Qingqing.

216
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:35,220
Mother, are you alright...

217
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,780
Mother, are you alright?

218
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:39,860
I'm fine.

219
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,740
Thankfully, Qingqing was here.

220
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,620
How were you pushing that cart?

221
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,780
You almost hit my mother.

222
00:09:44,790 --> 00:09:45,950
He didn't even pay attention.

223
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:47,460
It's you?

224
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:50,300
Aren't you the carter
from Ronghua Shop in the West Market?

225
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,890
Why are you moving goods here
in the East Market?

226
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:54,420
Shopkeeper Li.

227
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:55,220
Speak.

228
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,220
Could it be that you
are acting as a warehouse rat,

229
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,900
stealing goods to sell them on your own?

230
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:04,060
No...

231
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:05,740
It was her.

232
00:10:06,300 --> 00:10:07,720
She was the one who gave me silver,

233
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,460
and told me to ram into the old lady.

234
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:10,180
To think such a thing could happen!

235
00:10:10,180 --> 00:10:11,360
Hiring someone to hit a person?

236
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:12,860
What nonsense are you spouting?

237
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:14,200
I'll report this to the officials
and have you arrested!

238
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:15,900
How could anyone
do something so sinister?

239
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,080
Trying to run?

240
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:19,900
Stop right there!

241
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:22,820
(If not for Wang being investigated
by the Court of Judicial Review,)

242
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:25,200
(I would make Li Muyan get out
of the Pan Residence this very day.)

243
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:27,260
Good slap!

244
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:28,930
Hiring someone to harm
your own mother-in-law...

245
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:30,060
You are really something.

246
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:31,260
You slapped me?

247
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,340
This slap is
on behalf of the Pan family.

248
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,980
How do you expect others
to look at the Pan family

249
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:37,540
with you acting like this?

250
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:39,060
Who is this?

251
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:40,860
Isn't this General Pan's mistress?

252
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:41,580
She is so vicious.

253
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,700
Look at her seductive face.

254
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:43,460
A born troublemaker.

255
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,100
Exactly.

256
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,660
She stole Shopkeeper Li's husband
and is still causing trouble here.

257
00:10:46,660 --> 00:10:47,780
She should be driven out
of the Pan Residence soon.

258
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,180
What nonsense are you all talking about?

259
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,820
I don't know that man at all!

260
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:51,700
It's all Li Qingqing!

261
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:52,680
This is all her acting.

262
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:53,780
It's her.

263
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,220
Still making excuses?

264
00:10:55,230 --> 00:10:56,420
Drive her out of the Pan Residence soon.

265
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:56,860
Still faking it.

266
00:10:56,860 --> 00:10:58,180
Throw her out!

267
00:10:58,180 --> 00:10:59,690
She should be kicked out of the house!

268
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:05,860
Today's newspaper is hot off the press!

269
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:08,980
The mistress of the Pan Residence
caught red-handed hiring a hitman.

270
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:09,900
What does it say?

271
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,860
The newspaper says something
about striking the seductress.

272
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,660
How interesting.

273
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:13,060
(Pan mistress hires hitman)
Give me a copy.

274
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:13,980
(Wife slaps mistress on the spot)
The wicked woman caused trouble again.

275
00:11:13,980 --> 00:11:14,620
How exciting.

276
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:15,900
A reputation built over decades

277
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,740
has been ruined by a concubine.

278
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:19,300
You know,

279
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:22,100
a daughter-in-law who enters
the family halfway is just vicious.

280
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:25,300
The Tower Master's new poem
is filled with profound melancholy.

281
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:27,900
The city is guessing
the identity of the person in the poem.

282
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:28,980
Would you like a copy?

283
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:29,820
Give me one.

284
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:30,940
Come, give me one.

285
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:31,540
Here.

286
00:11:31,780 --> 00:11:32,300
Alright.

287
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,020
Let's look at the Tower Master's poem.

288
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,420
Hurry and read it to me.

289
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:36,060
I am illiterate.

290
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,100
Seafaring travelers speak of Yingzhou,

291
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:40,420
hidden among the misty waves,
truly hard to find.

292
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:41,700
People of Yue speak of Tianmu...

293
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:44,580
Not only are you skilled in business,

294
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:46,990
but you also possess such
brilliant literary talent in poetry.

295
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:49,260
The Wangshi Chronicle
has only published two issues,

296
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,660
yet your "Bring on the Liquor"

297
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:52,400
has already become
a massive hit throughout the capital.

298
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:55,820
See you not,

299
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:58,780
the Yellow River's waters
come from the sky,

300
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:02,460
rushing to the sea, never to return.

301
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,100
See you not,

302
00:12:04,580 --> 00:12:07,220
the bright mirrors in high halls
lamenting white hair,

303
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:11,020
like black silk in the morning,
turned to snow by dusk.

304
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:15,820
(How could Li's poems not be a hit?)

305
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:19,180
(As expected,
a classic lives on forever.)

306
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:21,700
(Wangshi Chronicle)
(Enjoy life's successes to the fullest,)

307
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:24,760
(and never let your golden goblet
face the moon in vain.)

308
00:12:25,540 --> 00:12:27,940
(Heaven made me talented,
and I must be of use.)

309
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:32,220
(A thousand gold pieces
scattered will all return again.)

310
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:41,470
♪Snowflakes settle gently
upon your brows♪

311
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:45,630
♪Your dark hair
brushes across my fingertips♪

312
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:48,150
♪Your smile♪

313
00:12:48,390 --> 00:12:50,670
♪Melts away the winter snow♪

314
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:54,350
♪One fleeting glance says more
than a thousand words♪

315
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:58,150
♪Yet I stand before you♪

316
00:12:58,870 --> 00:13:02,710
♪Unable to recognize your eyes♪

317
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:05,030
♪Though fate tries♪

318
00:13:05,030 --> 00:13:07,630
♪To make us pass each other by♪

319
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:11,270
♪I choose to make our story whole♪

320
00:13:11,510 --> 00:13:13,150
♪Though time slips by♪

321
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:14,910
♪As day turns into night♪

322
00:13:15,430 --> 00:13:19,470
♪I still remember
our days at Wangshi Tower♪

323
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:22,270
♪One glance at you lasts a lifetime♪

324
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:24,030
♪Blessed by fate♪

325
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:29,190
♪I believe this moment
will last forever♪

326
00:13:29,190 --> 00:13:31,630
♪Your smiling face♪

327
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:34,470
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

328
00:13:34,470 --> 00:13:38,110
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

329
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:42,070
♪And wander the world together♪

330
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:43,430
♪Holding you close♪

331
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:45,950
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

332
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,270
♪Your tenderness♪

333
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:51,150
♪Is the brightest moon♪

334
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:54,830
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

335
00:13:55,350 --> 00:13:58,670
♪Our love will never fade away♪

336
00:13:58,670 --> 00:14:01,110
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

337
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:05,910
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪

338
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:17,550
♪Your smiling face♪

339
